===Stark Industries / Stark International / Stark Enterprises===
* [[Amanda Armstrong (Earth-616)|Amanda Armstrong]] - President<ref>Although she has never been referred as ''President'', in {{cl|Invincible Iron Man Vol 4 3}}, C.E.O. [[Eric Lynch (Earth-616)|Eric Lynch]], reaching the [[Stark Industries Main Campus]] to take over the company's day-to-day management, found out that before entering in a comatose state, [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Tony Stark]] had put his biological mother, Amanda Armstrong, in charge of the daily operations. Usually, in corporate governance, the executive in charge of the day-to-day management is the '''President''', and this statement could be supported by [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|A.I. Tony Stark]]'s affirmation about Lynch in {{cl|Invincible Iron Man Vol 1 595}}: ''He thinks he should be the '''President''' of Stark Enterprises''.</ref>
* [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Anthony 'Tony' Stark]] - President, Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of the [[Stark Industries Board of Directors (Earth-616)|Board]]<ref>In {{cl|Invincible Iron Man #600}} [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Tony]] regained the President position from her mother [[Amanda Armstrong (Earth-616)|Amanda Armstrong]], as well as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman titles from [[Eric Lynch (Earth-616)|Eric Lynch]], who has been forced by Tony to resign.</ref>
* [[Eric Lynch (Earth-616)|Eric Lynch]] - Chief Executive Officer,{{r|Invincible Iron Man Vol 4 3}} Acting Chief Creative Officer{{r|Invincible Iron Man #599}} and Chairman of the [[Stark Industries Board of Directors (Earth-616)|Board]]{{r|Invincible Iron Man #593}}
* [[Friday Stark (Earth-616)|Friday]] - A.I. Manager of Day-to-Day Operations{{r|Invincible Iron Man Vol 3 9}}
* [[Mary Jane Watson (Earth-616)|Mary Jane Watson]] - Executive Assistant{{r|Invincible Iron Man Vol 3 10}} and Executive Administrator{{r|Invincible Iron Man Vol 3 11}}

